OL,6,FShe described the 1.5-degree
OL,7,Ftemperature rise as a "global
OL,8,Fshipwreck" - a nod to the Shakespeare
OL,9,Fplay they interrupted - and pointed to
OL,10,Frecent extreme weather events,
OL,11,Fincluding wildfires in California,
OL,12,Fdeadly floods in Valencia, and
OL,13,Fwidespread power outages in the UK as
OL,14,Fevidence of the climate crisis'
OL,15,Fimmediacy.
OL,17,FWeir, reflecting on his career in the
OL,18,Fshipyards of Tyneside, drew parallels
OL,19,Fbetween the government's failure to
OL,20,Faddress climate change and the decline
OL,21,Fof UK manufacturing due to inaction.
